net.librec.math.structure

Class SparseTensor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.librec.math.structure.SparseTensor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<TensorEntry>, DataSet

    public class SparseTensor
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataSet, java.lang.Iterable<TensorEntry>, java.io.Serializable
    Data Structure: Sparse Tensor

    For easy documentation, here we use (keys, value) to indicate each entry of a tensor, and index is used to indicate the position in which the entry is stored in the lists.

    Reference: Kolda and Bader, Tensor Decompositions and Applications, SIAM REVIEW, Vol. 51, No. 3, pp. 455â€“500
    Author:
    Guo Guibing
